Authorities have recovered stocks of stale beer and contraband cigarettes in Murang'a. The discovery was made by a multi-agency team at outlets in Kagundu-in shopping centre in Kandara. Murangâ€™a East deputy county commissioner Kepha Marube said the team acted on a tip-off. The stale beers were stacked in stores at various bars. They were bought from a retailer in Thika, Marube said. "We have also ordered the closure of three bars found operation with a joint licence," Marube said. The team seized 4,200 sticks of counterfeit cigarettes in Maragua town. The cigarettes had fake stamps. The team comprised of officers from KRA, Nacada, Kenya Bureau of Standards
and the department of public health.     